OL,3,CCustomers left to camp overnight in
OL,4,CGuernsey Airport after storm
OL,6,F"Disruption is the last resort.
OL,7,FHowever, safety of our passengers,
OL,8,Fcrew and aircraft is always our number
OL,9,Fone priority. While these
OL,10,Fcircumstances were out of our control,
OL,11,Fwe apologise for the inconvenience."
OL,13,FGuernsey Ports Chief Operating Officer
OL,14,FRoss Coppolo says: "We will be working
OL,15,Fwith the operator to help ensure in
OL,16,Ffuture that appropriate customer care
OL,17,Fis provided to passengers in the event
OL,18,Fof any late cancellations of scheduled
OL,19,Fservices.
